ðŸª¨ Progression Overhaul v0.1.0 â€” "Point of Humanity"
Focus: Primitive tools, early resource friction, and survival crafting depth.

âœ… Added Features
Pebble System:

Pebbles drop from stone when mined with sub-iron tools.

Added Andesite Pebbles, Diorite Pebbles, and Granite Pebbles.

2x2 crafting recipe combines 4 pebbles into their respective block.

Reverse crafting from blocks to pebbles also supported.

Sharp Stone:

Craftable from pebbles.

Used as an early flint-like tool part.

Plant Fiber:

Dropped from breaking grass/leaves.

Used as a primitive string replacement.

Tool Progression Changes:

Wooden sword durability drastically reduced (16 uses).

Removed stone sword.

Stone tools now require string/plant fiber in recipes.

Mining speed without tools significantly reduced.

Tools rebalanced to encourage progression.

Ore Drop Overhaul:

Iron ore drops raw iron when mined with sub-iron tools.

Drops itself (as block) only with iron-tier or better (supports Silk Touch).

Furnace Removal:

Standard furnace recipe removed to delay early smelting.

Intended to reintroduce alternate primitive smelting in future updates.

Armor Crafting:

Chainmail armor can now be crafted with chains.

Chains are now craftable from 3 iron nuggets.

Dirt Mining Drops:

Dirt and similar blocks drop a new item: Loose Dirt, when mined with tools below iron-tier.

Loose Dirt can be crafted back into Dirt (2x2 recipe).

Clay Furance Added.